lSsPnEwSCcf0M2L1pi0SX9Dyw_aYYTgDsjsOkPgJxXX_6J9TniHucx8-94Avsl5OxpdWNLv-1536x819.png 1536w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/ED92JsYURCxbuDeP_XUwGpC4RBUC3Kwor_w1haUTfAWhWD-mWt5pqfR0jywsmTfDjlSsPnEwSCcf0M2L1pi0SX9Dyw_aYYTgDsjsOkPgJxXX_6J9TniHucx8-94Avsl5OxpdWNLv-430x229.png 430w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/ED92JsYURCxbuDeP_XUwGpC4RBUC3Kwor_w1haUTfAWhWD-mWt5pqfR0jywsmTfDjlSsPnEwSCcf0M2L1pi0SX9Dyw_aYYTgDsjsOkPgJxXX_6J9TniHucx8-94Avsl5OxpdWNLv-645x344.png 645w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/ED92JsYURCxbuDeP_XUwGpC4RBUC3Kwor_w1haUTfAWhWD-mWt5pqfR0jywsmTfDjlSsPnEwSCcf0M2L1pi0SX9Dyw_aYYTgDsjsOkPgJxXX_6J9TniHucx8-94Avsl5OxpdWNLv-1068x569.png 1068w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/ED92JsYURCxbuDeP_XUwGpC4RBUC3Kwor_w1haUTfAWhWD-mWt5pqfR0jywsmTfDjlSsPnEwSCcf0M2L1pi0SX9Dyw_aYYTgDsjsOkPgJxXX_6J9TniHucx8-94Avsl5OxpdWNLv-460x245.png 460w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/ED92JsYURCxbuDeP_XUwGpC4RBUC3Kwor_w1haUTfAWhWD-mWt5pqfR0jywsmTfDjlSsPnEwSCcf0M2L1pi0SX9Dyw_aYYTgDsjsOkPgJxXX_6J9TniHucx8-94Avsl5OxpdWNLv-1074x573.png 1074w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/ED92JsYURCxbuDeP_XUwGpC4RBUC3Kwor_w1haUTfAWhWD-mWt5pqfR0jywsmTfDjlSsPnEwSCcf0M2L1pi0SX9Dyw_aYYTgDsjsOkPgJxXX_6J9TniHucx8-94Avsl5OxpdWNLv-512x273.png 512w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/ED92JsYURCxbuDeP_XUwGpC4RBUC3Kwor_w1haUTfAWhWD-mWt5pqfR0jywsmTfDjlSsPnEwSCcf0M2L1pi0SX9Dyw_aYYTgDsjsOkPgJxXX_6J9TniHucx8-94Avsl5OxpdWNLv-707x377.png 707w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/ED92JsYURCxbuDeP_XUwGpC4RBUC3Kwor_w1haUTfAWhWD-mWt5pqfR0jywsmTfDjlSsPnEwSCcf0M2L1pi0SX9Dyw_aYYTgDsjsOkPgJxXX_6J9TniHucx8-94Avsl5OxpdWNLv-600x320.png 600w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/ED92JsYURCxbuDeP_XUwGpC4RBUC3Kwor_w1haUTfAWhWD-mWt5pqfR0jywsmTfDjlSsPnEwSCcf0M2L1pi0SX9Dyw_aYYTgDsjsOkPgJxXX_6J9TniHucx8-94Avsl5OxpdWNLv-500x267.png 500w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>You’ll see several page template options appear. Choose the Home option.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img width=\"1600\" height=\"818\" src=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-03-14-at-2.48.37-PM.jpg\" alt=\"Choose the Home option for the conference page\" class=\"wp-image-2426570\" srcset=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-03-14-at-2.48.37-PM.jpg 1600w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-03-14-at-2.48.37-PM-300x153.jpg 300w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-03-14-at-2.48.37-PM-665x340.jpg 665w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-03-14-at-2.48.37-PM-140x72.jpg 140w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-03-14-at-2.48.37-PM-768x393.jpg 768w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-03-14-at-2.48.37-PM-1536x785.jpg 1536w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-03-14-at-2.48.37-PM-430x220.jpg 430w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-03-14-at-2.48.37-PM-645x330.jpg 645w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-03-14-at-2.48.37-PM-1068x546.jpg 1068w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-03-14-at-2.48.37-PM-460x235.jpg 460w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-03-14-at-2.48.37-PM-1074x549.jpg 1074w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-03-14-at-2.48.37-PM-512x262.jpg 512w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-03-14-at-2.48.37-PM-707x361.jpg 707w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-03-14-at-2.48.37-PM-600x307.jpg 600w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-03-14-at-2.48.37-PM-500x256.jpg 500w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Enter your email address in the prompt and select Subscribe and Start Importing to add the page to your website. If additional plugins are needed for this starter template to work correctly, Kadence will automatically install them for you. Once it’s done importing, you can select Finish and view the page.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>It may not look like a conference website yet, but with a few additions and customizations, you’ll see things start to take shape very quickly.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Customize the content</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The next step in this process is to change the content provided on the page so that the website becomes your own. To begin editing the page, click on Edit Page at the top of the admin toolbar.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The Kadence theme has a Design Library with stock images that you can use throughout your web page. Also important are the <a href=\"https://www.kadencewp.com/kadence-theme/knowledge-base/customize-settings/how-to-setup-page-post-settings/?_ics=1650296382672&amp;irclickid=~bgimsjnjheb9~2XORSX3UKLECIDEGDIPHzBFGwxolh-92YXOEzvl\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Page Settings and Kadence Blocks Controls</a> at the top. These will help you control your page&#8217;s layout, add columns, and alter other elements on the page.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The Kadence Starter Template that we’ve chosen is well-equipped with what you need for a conference website, but you’ll want to make text changes and add your content, conference titles, and event information.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Add your main conference page</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Now that your homepage is up and running, you’ll want to utilize the event feature with The Events Calendar to create your main conference page. This is the landing page where prospective attendees can register for and purchase tickets to your conference.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To do this, head over to <strong>Events &gt; Add New</strong> in the WordPress Dashboard. You’ll see prompts to fill in the information, including the conference&#8217;s title, date and time, organizer, and venue. This is also the place to add your conference registration.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img width=\"1166\" height=\"1290\" src=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-18-at-1.38.30-PM.png\" alt=\"Add your main conference page with The Events Calendar\" class=\"wp-image-2426577\" srcset=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-18-at-1.38.30-PM.png 1166w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-18-at-1.38.30-PM-271x300.png 271w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-18-at-1.38.30-PM-665x736.png 665w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-18-at-1.38.30-PM-77x85.png 77w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-18-at-1.38.30-PM-768x850.png 768w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-18-at-1.38.30-PM-430x476.png 430w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-18-at-1.38.30-PM-645x714.png 645w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-18-at-1.38.30-PM-1068x1182.png 1068w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-18-at-1.38.30-PM-460x509.png 460w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-18-at-1.38.30-PM-1074x1188.png 1074w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-18-at-1.38.30-PM-512x566.png 512w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-18-at-1.38.30-PM-996x1102.png 996w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-18-at-1.38.30-PM-479x530.png 479w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-18-at-1.38.30-PM-300x332.png 300w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-18-at-1.38.30-PM-600x664.png 600w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-18-at-1.38.30-PM-500x553.png 500w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1166px) 100vw, 1166px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>Install Event Tickets</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>To add tickets or registrations to your conference, you’ll also need our <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/products/wordpress-event-tickets/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Event Tickets</a> plugin. Don’t worry, it’s free, and it comes with a <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/knowledgebase/k/tickets-commerce/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">built-in ecommerce solution</a> that easily integrates with PayPal and Stripe. If you’d like additional ecommerce options, like WooCommerce and Easy Digital Downloads, as well as custom registration fields, we’d recommend upgrading to our premium <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/products/wordpress-event-tickets/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Event Tickets Plus</a> plugin.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Once you <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/knowledgebase/k/downloading-and-installing-the-plugin/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">install Event Tickets</a>, you’ll automatically see a ticket block available so that you can <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/knowledgebase/k/making-tickets/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">create your conference website ticket</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img width=\"1244\" height=\"1160\" src=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-18-at-2.01.34-PM.png\" alt=\"Tickets for main conference page created with Event Tickets\" class=\"wp-image-2426578\" srcset=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-18-at-2.01.34-PM.png 1244w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-18-at-2.01.34-PM-300x280.png 300w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-18-at-2.01.34-PM-665x620.png 665w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-18-at-2.01.34-PM-91x85.png 91w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-18-at-2.01.34-PM-768x716.png 768w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-18-at-2.01.34-PM-430x401.png 430w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-18-at-2.01.34-PM-645x601.png 645w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-18-at-2.01.34-PM-1068x996.png 1068w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-18-at-2.01.34-PM-460x429.png 460w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-18-at-2.01.34-PM-1074x1001.png 1074w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-18-at-2.01.34-PM-512x477.png 512w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-18-at-2.01.34-PM-1182x1102.png 1182w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-18-at-2.01.34-PM-568x530.png 568w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-18-at-2.01.34-PM-600x559.png 600w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-18-at-2.01.34-PM-500x466.png 500w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1244px) 100vw, 1244px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>Create pages for your speakers</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Next, you’ll want to create individual event pages for each of your conference speakers. You’ll use the same process as you used to create your main conference registration page. So head back over to <strong>Events &gt; Add New</strong> in the WordPress Dashboard to make your first session. Use your speaker’s name to title your page. Include a description of the event, date and time, and information about where the event will take place. Repeat this process for each of your speakers.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img width=\"1152\" height=\"1270\" src=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-19-at-6.44.41-AM.png\" alt=\"Individual speaker page for conference website\" class=\"wp-image-2426579\" srcset=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-19-at-6.44.41-AM.png 1152w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-19-at-6.44.41-AM-272x300.png 272w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-19-at-6.44.41-AM-665x733.png 665w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-19-at-6.44.41-AM-77x85.png 77w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-19-at-6.44.41-AM-768x847.png 768w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-19-at-6.44.41-AM-430x474.png 430w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-19-at-6.44.41-AM-645x711.png 645w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-19-at-6.44.41-AM-1068x1177.png 1068w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-19-at-6.44.41-AM-460x507.png 460w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-19-at-6.44.41-AM-1074x1184.png 1074w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-19-at-6.44.41-AM-512x564.png 512w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-19-at-6.44.41-AM-1000x1102.png 1000w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-19-at-6.44.41-AM-481x530.png 481w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-19-at-6.44.41-AM-300x331.png 300w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-19-at-6.44.41-AM-600x661.png 600w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-19-at-6.44.41-AM-500x551.png 500w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1152px) 100vw, 1152px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Use different locations or links for each of your speakers to take place simultaneously. If you have more than one track for your speakers throughout your conference, you can simply use the same time for each of your speakers to create two separate conference “rooms.” In the same vein, if you have speakers one after another, use individual events for each one.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Add lots of links</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Next, add links so that people know how to access your conference. You can choose whether you&#8217;d like to <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/knowledgebase/k/creating-a-virtual-event/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">host your conference</a> over Zoom, Facebook Live, YouTube Live, or Webex, and embed a link directly on your event page with our <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/products/wordpress-virtual-events/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Virtual Events</a> plugin.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>There are many options regarding how to display your conference links so that attendees know where they are going. By showing your link directly on the event page, users will have easy access to your conference so that they don’t get lost. Alternatively, if you’d prefer <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/knowledgebase/k/security-and-protected-content-for-virtual-events/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">only to provide access</a> to your conference once users purchase tickets, you can also opt to do that.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Once they’re in, decide if you’d like to keep chat enabled on your platform of choice. Doing so would allow users to comment throughout the conference. In this case, we’d recommend assigning a moderator so that the speaker isn’t presenting while also managing comments and questions.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Feel free to turn off this feature if you’d like to keep viewers’ attention focused on the speaker. To engage in the conversation before and after the conference, consider using a community tool like <a href=\"https://www.buddyboss.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">BuddyBoss</a> or a P2P chat plugin like <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/rumbletalk-chat-a-chat-with-themes/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Rumble Chat</a> to add chat and discussion as part of your virtual conference.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Bonus Points</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Now that you’ve created your conference sessions, your conference website is functional and ready to accept registrations. But there are a few “nice-to-haves” that you can implement on your website to make it even better.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To start, you can use our handy <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/extensions/change-labels-events-venues-organizers/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">relabeler extension</a> to replace the word “event” with “conference” or “session” throughout your WordPress site. This will help drive the point home that this is a conference and add another layer of professionalism to your website.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In addition, we’d recommend utilizing <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/knowledgebase/k/event-categories/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Event Categories</a> for each of your conferences. This will allow you to set up individual calendars and schedules on unique category pages, which can be especially useful if you have speakers on multiple tracks. In this case, you can set a separate category for each track and create individual pages for each of your tracks. Attendees can then visit each page separately to get a sense of what is going on at any given time.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can also add your calendar to your homepage as well. Simply add a shortcode block and use the <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/knowledgebase/k/embedding-calendar-views-with-the-tribe_events-shortcode/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">[tribe_events]</a> shortcode. From there, you can add attributes to select the calendar view, category, or a number of other options.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img width=\"1128\" height=\"794\" src=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-18-at-1.01.59-PM.png\" alt=\"Shortcode to display conference calendar\" class=\"wp-image-2426583\" srcset=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-18-at-1.01.59-PM.png 1128w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-18-at-1.01.59-PM-300x211.png 300w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-18-at-1.01.59-PM-665x468.png 665w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-18-at-1.01.59-PM-121x85.png 121w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-18-at-1.01.59-PM-768x541.png 768w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-18-at-1.01.59-PM-430x303.png 430w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-18-at-1.01.59-PM-645x454.png 645w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-18-at-1.01.59-PM-1068x752.png 1068w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-18-at-1.01.59-PM-460x324.png 460w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-18-at-1.01.59-PM-1074x756.png 1074w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-18-at-1.01.59-PM-512x360.png 512w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-18-at-1.01.59-PM-707x498.png 707w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-18-at-1.01.59-PM-600x422.png 600w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-18-at-1.01.59-PM-500x352.png 500w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1128px) 100vw, 1128px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Once you add the rest of your content, on the frontend of your site, you’ll see something like this:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img width=\"780\" height=\"1362\" src=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-19-at-6.50.27-AM.png\" alt=\"Shortcode displays conference calendar on the front end\" class=\"wp-image-2426584\" srcset=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-19-at-6.50.27-AM.png 780w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-19-at-6.50.27-AM-172x300.png 172w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-19-at-6.50.27-AM-586x1024.png 586w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-19-at-6.50.27-AM-49x85.png 49w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-19-at-6.50.27-AM-768x1341.png 768w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-19-at-6.50.27-AM-430x751.png 430w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-19-at-6.50.27-AM-645x1126.png 645w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-19-at-6.50.27-AM-460x803.png 460w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-19-at-6.50.27-AM-512x894.png 512w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-19-at-6.50.27-AM-631x1102.png 631w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-19-at-6.50.27-AM-304x530.png 304w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-19-at-6.50.27-AM-300x524.png 300w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-19-at-6.50.27-AM-458x800.png 458w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-19-at-6.50.27-AM-500x873.png 500w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 780px) 100vw, 780px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>Virtual Events for the win</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>And that’s it! You’ve now created your conference website. Feel free to take a look at our completed conference website demo <a href=\"https://demo.theeventscalendar.com/conference/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">here</a>.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Creating a conference event website on WordPress is easy with <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/products/wordpress-virtual-events/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Virtual Events</a>. With it, you can seamlessly add online meetings and webinars, integrate with your favorite online meeting tools, and highlight events as virtual and hybrid right on your WordPress calendar.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Want to learn more about our plugins? Check out our <a href=\"https://demo.theeventscalendar.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">demo site</a> to see our plugins in action and <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/demo/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">request one</a> to try it out for yourself.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/blog/tips/how-to-set-up-a-conference-event-website-on-wordpress/\">Conference Website Inspiration and Setup</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:9;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:60:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:57:\"Introducing New Shortcode and Elementor Widget Attributes\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:169:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/blog/news/introducing-new-shortcode-and-elementor-widget-attributes/?utm_source=theeventscalendar&utm_medium=referral&utm_campaign=rss-feed\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Thu, 21 Apr 2022 13:48:11 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:10:\"What\'s New\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"blog\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:40:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/?p=2425908\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:670:\"<p>With our latest release of Events Calendar Pro 5.13.0, we&#8217;re excited to announce some new additions to our [tribe_events] shortcode! You&#8217;ll be happy to know that these were features that several of our users were asking for in our Feature Requests forum. Here&#8217;s what one of our users asked for: It&#8217;s [currently] possible to display&#8230;</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/blog/news/introducing-new-shortcode-and-elementor-widget-attributes/\">Introducing New Shortcode and Elementor Widget Attributes</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5:\"Jaime\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:10924:\"\n<p>With our latest release of <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-notes/events-calendar-pro/events-calendar-pro-5-13-0/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Events Calendar Pro 5.13.0</a>, we&#8217;re excited to announce some new additions to our <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/knowledgebase/k/embedding-calendar-views-with-the-tribe_events-shortcode/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">[tribe_events]</a> shortcode! You&#8217;ll be happy to know that these were features that several of our users were asking for in our <a href=\"https://app.productstash.io/the-events-calendar-suite-roadmap#ideas\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Feature Requests</a> forum. </p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://app.loopedin.io/the-events-calendar-suite-roadmap?idea=6190a923023528002dc03101#/ideas\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Here&#8217;s</a> what one of our users asked for:</p>\n\n\n\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>It&#8217;s [currently] possible to display a single category by using a shortcode like: [tribe_events view=&#8221;list&#8221; category=&#8221;mycat&#8221;]</p><p>How about excluding one or more categories by using a shortcode like: [tribe_events view=&#8221;list&#8221; exclude-category=&#8221;mycat&#8221;]</p></blockquote>\n\n\n\n<p>We want you to know that we read all of your suggestions, so keep them coming!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>So without further ado, let&#8217;s look at the shiny new features, hot off the presses!</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"h-new-shortcode-attributes\">New shortcode attributes</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>As you may know, you can add attributes to the [tribe_events] shortcode to customize the calendar of events that you display on any WordPress page or post. With this release, you&#8217;ll find even more ways to make that happen.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>First off, we&#8217;ve added the ability to exclude any category or tag from your shortcode calendar. Simply add the &#8220;exclude-category&#8221; or &#8220;exclude-tag&#8221; attribute to your shortcode, so it&#8217;ll look something like this: </p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img width=\"1216\" height=\"220\" src=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-21-at-6.45.36-AM.png\" alt=\"New shortcode attributes\" class=\"wp-image-2426093\" srcset=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-21-at-6.45.36-AM.png 1216w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-21-at-6.45.36-AM-300x54.png 300w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-21-at-6.45.36-AM-665x120.png 665w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-21-at-6.45.36-AM-140x25.png 140w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-21-at-6.45.36-AM-768x139.png 768w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-21-at-6.45.36-AM-430x78.png 430w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-21-at-6.45.36-AM-645x117.png 645w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-21-at-6.45.36-AM-1068x193.png 1068w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-21-at-6.45.36-AM-460x83.png 460w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-21-at-6.45.36-AM-1074x194.png 1074w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-21-at-6.45.36-AM-512x93.png 512w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-21-at-6.45.36-AM-707x128.png 707w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-21-at-6.45.36-AM-600x109.png 600w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-21-at-6.45.36-AM-500x90.png 500w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1216px) 100vw, 1216px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>You&#8217;ll see all of your events on the front end, except those belonging to the category or tag you&#8217;ve chosen to hide. This attribute can be useful if you&#8217;re trying to remove specific events from the calendar. In this case, use the shortcode to exclude the categories or tags for all of your private events, and you&#8217;ll automatically remove them from public view.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Next, we&#8217;ve added venue, organizer, and event author attributes. You can now display events for only a particular venue, specific organizer, or single event author with a shortcode. You can use these attributes to customize the appearance of your calendar further and create a separate calendar for each of your venues or organizers. With the event author option, you can use individual pages for each of your author&#8217;s events.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img width=\"1210\" height=\"214\" src=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-21-at-7.11.11-AM.png\" alt=\"New shortcode attributes\" class=\"wp-image-2426107\" srcset=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-21-at-7.11.11-AM.png 1210w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-21-at-7.11.11-AM-300x53.png 300w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-21-at-7.11.11-AM-665x118.png 665w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-21-at-7.11.11-AM-140x25.png 140w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-21-at-7.11.11-AM-768x136.png 768w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-21-at-7.11.11-AM-430x76.png 430w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-21-at-7.11.11-AM-645x114.png 645w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-21-at-7.11.11-AM-1068x189.png 1068w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-21-at-7.11.11-AM-460x81.png 460w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-21-at-7.11.11-AM-1074x190.png 1074w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-21-at-7.11.11-AM-512x91.png 512w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-21-at-7.11.11-AM-707x125.png 707w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-21-at-7.11.11-AM-600x106.png 600w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-21-at-7.11.11-AM-500x88.png 500w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1210px) 100vw, 1210px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"h-elementor-widget-attributes\">Elementor widget attributes</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>In addition to these new shortcodes attributes, you&#8217;ll now find that you can use these same options with <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/knowledgebase/k/native-elementor-widgets-for-events-calendar-pro/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Elementor&#8217;s native widgets</a>. For example, with Elementor&#8217;s Events View widget, you can now exclude certain categories and only let users see the events from categories you&#8217;d like them to see.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Lastly, we&#8217;ve added Elementor support for filtering events by author, organizer, and venue on the Events View Elementor widget. This functionality works just like it does with the Events Calendar Pro shortcode.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img width=\"2162\" height=\"1122\" src=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-21-at-6.35.34-AM.png\" alt=\"Elementor Events View widget \" class=\"wp-image-2426089\" srcset=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-21-at-6.35.34-AM.png 2162w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-21-at-6.35.34-AM-300x156.png 300w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-21-at-6.35.34-AM-665x345.png 665w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-21-at-6.35.34-AM-140x73.png 140w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-21-at-6.35.34-AM-768x399.png 768w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-21-at-6.35.34-AM-1536x797.png 1536w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-21-at-6.35.34-AM-2048x1063.png 2048w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-21-at-6.35.34-AM-430x223.png 430w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-21-at-6.35.34-AM-645x335.png 645w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-21-at-6.35.34-AM-2000x1038.png 2000w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-21-at-6.35.34-AM-1068x554.png 1068w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-21-at-6.35.34-AM-460x239.png 460w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-21-at-6.35.34-AM-1602x831.png 1602w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-21-at-6.35.34-AM-1074x557.png 1074w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-21-at-6.35.34-AM-512x266.png 512w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-21-at-6.35.34-AM-1611x836.png 1611w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-21-at-6.35.34-AM-707x367.png 707w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-21-at-6.35.34-AM-600x311.png 600w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-04-21-at-6.35.34-AM-500x259.png 500w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2162px) 100vw, 2162px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-white-color has-tec-blue-background-color has-text-color has-background\"><a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/products/wordpress-events-calendar/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"><strong>Get Events Calendar Pro Now!</strong></a></p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"h-so-many-ways-to-filter\">So many ways to filter!</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Love adding filters to your calendar? Of course, you do! You can easily create customized calendars for your viewers with a few simple keystrokes. If you love filtering events as much as we do, check out our <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/products/wordpress-calendar-filter-bar/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Filter Bar</a> plugin. This plugin adds front-end options that allow your users to do the filtering, narrowing down their event options by category, day of the week, price, and more! Feel free to check out our <a href=\"https://demo.theeventscalendar.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">demo site</a> to see our plugins in action.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/blog/news/introducing-new-shortcode-and-elementor-widget-attributes/\">Introducing New Shortcode and Elementor Widget Attributes</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}}}s:27:\"http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom\";a:1:{s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:3:{s:4:\"href\";s:35:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/feed/\";s:3:\"rel\";s:4:\"self\";s:4:\"type\";s:19:\"application/rss+xml\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:44:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/syndication/\";a:2:{s:12:\"updatePeriod\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"\n	hourly	\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:15:\"updateFrequency\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"\n	1	\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\