yword placement\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"SEO keywords\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:27:\"https://aioseo.com/?p=76045\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:435:\"<p>Want to know how to add SEO keywords in WordPress? SEO keywords are central to any SEO campaign as they help your content rank higher on search engine results pages. They are also an important element that helps boost your&#8230;</p>\nThe post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-add-seo-keywords-in-wordpress/\">How to Add SEO Keywords in WordPress (Boost CTR & Rankings)</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"Kato Nkhoma\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:14382:\"<p>Want to know how to add SEO keywords in WordPress?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>SEO keywords are central to any SEO campaign as they help your content rank higher on search engine results pages. They are also an important element that helps boost your clickthrough rate (CTR) — especially if you <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-find-long-tail-keywords-and-increase-organic-traffic/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" title=\"use keywords that meet search intent\">use keywords that meet search intent</a>. </p>\n\n\n\n<h2>What are SEO Keywords?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>SEO keywords are words and phrases you want your content to rank for on search results. They’re a crucial element of <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/ultimate-wordpress-seo-guide/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" title=\"your SEO strategy\">your SEO strategy</a> as they help direct your content creation. That’s because each piece of content you publish must be targeted at a particular keyword that your target audience is interested in.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To find the right SEO keywords for your brand, you must conduct keyword research. This is the practice of using tools to discover the phrases and words your target audience uses the most as they search for a product, solution, or topic in your niche. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Then, when you feature these SEO keywords in your content, search engines know that your content is relevant to a search query made. As a result, they’ll serve it up to users.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>How to Add SEO Keywords in WordPress — The Easy Way</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Once you’ve conducted your keyword research and discovered the ones to use in each post, you must also know how to use them in your content strategically.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here are a few tips on how and where to place your SEO keywords:&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Post Title</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Your title is the first thing readers see on search engine results pages (SERPs), so it&#8217;s best to include your SEO keyword. This way, you’ll be able to prove search intent quickly, resulting in high clickthrough rates. Make sure to frontload your SEO keyword as much as possible. This ensures that it remains visible, even if your title gets truncated, particularly when viewed on smaller screens.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To add an SEO keyword in your title, scroll down to the bottom of your post or page, where you’ll find a text box for editing your title.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"183\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/how-to-add-SEO-keywords-in-wordpress-post-title-1.png\" alt=\"Knowing how to add SEO keywords in WordPress involves including them in the post title.\" class=\"wp-image-77771\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/how-to-add-SEO-keywords-in-wordpress-post-title-1.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/how-to-add-SEO-keywords-in-wordpress-post-title-1-300x78.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/how-to-add-SEO-keywords-in-wordpress-post-title-1-600x157.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>To avoid having your title being cut off on SERPs, keep it within 60 characters.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Headline</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The headline is the first element readers see on your page. It’s different from your SEO title in that the SEO title is what people see on SERPs, while the headline is crafted for people who are already on a page. Once search engines are on a page, it’s also one of the first elements they use to determine what the page is about. Therefore, including your SEO keywords will improve your chances of ranking for relevant search queries.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can add your SEO keyword in your headline as you type it right at the top of the page.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"700\" height=\"240\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-add-seo-keywords-to-wordpress-headline.png\" alt=\"Another strategic place to add SEO keywords is in the headline.\" class=\"wp-image-76157\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-add-seo-keywords-to-wordpress-headline.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-add-seo-keywords-to-wordpress-headline-300x103.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-add-seo-keywords-to-wordpress-headline-600x206.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Try as much as possible to frontload your keyword. This way, users and search engines quickly get what your post is about. This way your <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/best-wordpress-headline-analyzer-tool/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" title=\"headline will be optimized\">headline will be optimized</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Header Tags</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Header tags are primarily used to separate sections on a web page. However, header tags are not just effective at organizing the information. You can optimize your content by including your SEO keywords in them. Search engines and readers use header tags to understand the context of your web page. Therefore, including your SEO keywords helps them quickly do so.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>These can be easily added as you write your content, as with the headline.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Introduction and Conclusion</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Another important place to add your SEO keyword is in the introduction of your article, preferably the first 150 words. This will help you immediately grab your readers&#8217; attention and encourage them to continue reading. Seeing the keyword in the keyword will convince them that your content will meet their search intent. As a result, they&#8217;ll spend more time on your page, signalling to search engines that your content is valuable.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Body Copy</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>You should also sprinkle your SEO keywords in your body copy. Don&#8217;t overdo it, though, as this could be deemed keyword stuffing. Instead, strike the right balance, so search engines know that your content matches the user’s search query. Besides, keyword stuffing also detracts from your page&#8217;s user experience (UX).</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>URL</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Your URL is another important place to add your SEO keywords. For one, it helps search engines know what your content is about. Secondly, because it appears right below the title on SERPs, it’s one of the first things users see. Finally, if your keyword is in the URL, it cements the fact that your content will meet their search intent.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>While WordPress generates a URL for you based on your headline, you must customize it to include your keyword. This is very easy to do with a tool like AIOSEO. Simply save your draft, then head to the post settings on the right-hand side of the screen. Scroll down until you find the “Permalink” setting.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"308\" height=\"357\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-add-seo-keywords-to-wordpress-url.png\" alt=\"Knowing how to add SEO keywords in WordPress includes placing your keywords in the URL.\" class=\"wp-image-76159\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-add-seo-keywords-to-wordpress-url.png 308w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-add-seo-keywords-to-wordpress-url-259x300.png 259w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 308px) 100vw, 308px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<h3>Meta Description</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-write-meta-descriptions-for-seo/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" title=\"meta description\">meta description</a> is the last element of your page or post that appears on the results snippet on SERPs. Because of this, it’s another strategic place to add your SEO keyword. Again, with AIOSEO, editing your meta description is easy. Just scroll to the bottom of your post/page to the “Meta Description” field.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"700\" height=\"200\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-add-seo-keywords-to-wordpress-meta-description.png\" alt=\"The meta description is another great place to add your SEO keywords. \" class=\"wp-image-76160\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-add-seo-keywords-to-wordpress-meta-description.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-add-seo-keywords-to-wordpress-meta-description-300x86.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-add-seo-keywords-to-wordpress-meta-description-600x171.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>As with the other elements on your post, front-load the keyword as much as possible.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Once you’ve filled in the Post Title, Meta Description, and URL Slug field, AIOSEO will show you a preview of what the snippet will look like on SERPs.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"823\" height=\"295\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/how-to-add-SEO-keywords-in-wordpress-snippet-1.png\" alt=\"AIOSEO shows you a snippet of what your meta data will look like on SERPs.\" class=\"wp-image-77778\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/how-to-add-SEO-keywords-in-wordpress-snippet-1.png 823w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/how-to-add-SEO-keywords-in-wordpress-snippet-1-300x108.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/how-to-add-SEO-keywords-in-wordpress-snippet-1-768x275.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/how-to-add-SEO-keywords-in-wordpress-snippet-1-600x215.png 600w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Make sure everything is correct before you publish.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Image Name and Alt Text</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>If you include images in your content (as you should), include your keyword in the image name and the alt text. The easiest way to add <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-write-alt-text-for-images-for-seo-3-easy-tips/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" title=\"image alt text\">image alt text</a> is to upload your image then fill in the “Alt Text” field on the “Select or Upload Media” page.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"325\" height=\"505\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-add-seo-keywords-to-wordpress-image-alt-text-1.png\" alt=\"Add SEO keywords to your alt text.\" class=\"wp-image-76166\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-add-seo-keywords-to-wordpress-image-alt-text-1.png 325w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-add-seo-keywords-to-wordpress-image-alt-text-1-193x300.png 193w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 325px) 100vw, 325px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>You can also add alt text to your image after uploading it, especially if you’re using the block editor. Just click on the image, and the settings for that block will open up, including the “Alt Text” field:</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"374\" height=\"448\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-add-seo-keywords-to-wordpress-image-alt-text.png\" alt=\"Adding image alt text in the block editor is as easy as clicking on the image and editing the alt text in the field provided. \" class=\"wp-image-76167\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-add-seo-keywords-to-wordpress-image-alt-text.png 374w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-add-seo-keywords-to-wordpress-image-alt-text-250x300.png 250w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 374px) 100vw, 374px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Simply fill in your alt text, and that’s it! You’ve added your SEO keyword in WordPress.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Now You Know How to Add SEO Keywords in WordPress, What Next?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Adding your SEO keywords in WordPress is not the end goal of <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/seo-checklist/\" title=\"your SEO strategy\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">your SEO strategy</a>. Once your post is live, you must <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/best-seo-rank-tracker/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" title=\"track your keywords\">track your keywords</a>. You must keep an eye on how your keywords are performing. Doing so will help you know if you’re making headway or whether you need to adjust your strategy.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>An excellent way of doing this is by <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-set-up-google-analytics-on-a-wordpress-site/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" title=\"connecting your WordPress site to Google Analytics\">connecting your WordPress site to Google Analytics</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you need an easy way to do this from right within your WordPress Dashboard, you can install a Google Analytics plugin like <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/\" title=\"MonsterInsights\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">MonsterInsights</a>. It’s the best Google Analytics plugin for WordPress. Among other insights, MonsterInsights will show you the keyphrases:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Drive the most traffic to your website</li><li>That aren’t performing well</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>If you discover keywords that are not bringing in the desired results, you can work on other ranking measures. For example, you can build more backlinks to the content or encourage more social sharing. You can also rework the content if it’s not meeting user intent.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Ready to Add SEO Keywords in WordPress? It’s Easy with AIOSEO</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>As you’ve seen, SEO keywords are the foundation of every SEO campaign. Placing them properly in your content is critical to increasing your chances of ranking. That’s why you need a powerful SEO tool that makes SEO keyword placement easy. You need a tool like AIOSEO. With AIOSEO, you can, besides adding SEO keywords:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Create sitemaps</li><li>Build powerful internal links</li><li>Create redirects</li><li>And much more.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>So, go ahead and <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" title=\"download AIOSEO today\">download AIOSEO today</a> and supercharge your WordPress SEO.</p>The post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-add-seo-keywords-in-wordpress/\">How to Add SEO Keywords in WordPress (Boost CTR & Rankings)</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:61:\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-add-seo-keywords-in-wordpress/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:1;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:88:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:59:\"29 Link Building Statistics to Help Power Your SEO Strategy\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:112:\"https://aioseo.com/link-building-statistics/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=link-building-statistics\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:53:\"https://aioseo.com/link-building-statistics/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Thu, 05 May 2022 15:19:24 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:6:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"Blog\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"SEO News\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"backlinks\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:14:\"internal links\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"link building\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:5;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:3:\"SEO\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:27:\"https://aioseo.com/?p=88674\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:441:\"<p>Looking for some link building statistics to inspire your next campaign? Link building is one of the pillar elements of effective SEO campaigns and, as such, requires careful planning. One way you can do that is to get current link-building&#8230;</p>\nThe post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/link-building-statistics/\">29 Link Building Statistics to Help Power Your SEO Strategy</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"Kato Nkhoma\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:16338:\"<p>Looking for some link building statistics to inspire your next campaign?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Link building is one of the pillar elements of <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/seo-hacks-to-grow-your-traffic/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">effective SEO campaigns</a> and, as such, requires careful planning. One way you can do that is to get current link-building stats so you know the lay of the land.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>But first, let&#8217;s get a few basics covered.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>What is Link Building?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Link building is the practice of proactively increasing the number of inbound links to a webpage. Effective link building requires focusing on high-quality links, not just quantity. It&#8217;s also important that the links you build are relevant to your niche, industry, and topic. This is because links are a vote of confidence in the quality of your content. Therefore, the more relevant a backlink is, the more value it has.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>No matter what niche or industry you&#8217;re in, link building is a vital element of executing an impactful digital marketing strategy.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>A few benefits of Link building include:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>Traffic generation</strong>: You get to tap into the host site&#8217;s audience as they can click on your link and land on your website.</li><li><strong>Brand awareness</strong>: When other sites link to yours, you gain brand exposure, resulting in a boost in brand awareness.</li><li><strong>Increase in domain authority (DA)</strong>: DA is a metric created by Moz to measure how likely a website will rank well on Google search and other search engine results pages (SERPs). The higher the DA, the more likely you will rank for our chosen keywords.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>With that out of the way, let&#8217;s dive right into the most important link building stats you need to know.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>General Link Building Statistics</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Before we zero in on some specific link building statistics you can use to fine-tune your campaigns, let&#8217;s first look at some general link building statistics.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>1. <a href=\"https://backlinko.com/content-study\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">94% of all the content</a> on the internet doesn&#8217;t have a backlink. This means brands that proactively build backlinks are already at an advantage in running successful content marketing campaigns.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>2. <a href=\"http://ww2.conductor.com/rs/conductor2/images/SEO%20Enterprise%20Benchmark%20Study_Conductor.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">41% of enterprise companies</a> say link building is the most challenging aspect of SEO.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"688\" height=\"474\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/link-building-statistics-difficult-seo-aspects.png\" alt=\"Link building statistics show that building backlinks is one of the hardest things for large enterprises. \" class=\"wp-image-88688\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/link-building-statistics-difficult-seo-aspects.png 688w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/link-building-statistics-difficult-seo-aspects-300x207.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/link-building-statistics-difficult-seo-aspects-600x413.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 688px) 100vw, 688px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>3. <a href=\"https://aira.net/state-of-link-building/the-impact-of-link-building/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">85% of marketers</a> believe links will still play an essential role in how search engines rank websites five years from now.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>4. <a href=\"http://ww2.conductor.com/rs/conductor2/images/SEO%20Enterprise%20Benchmark%20Study_Conductor.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">13% of SEO experts</a> cite link building as the most valuable SEO tactic.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Importance of Link Building for SEO</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Is link building really important for SEO?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Yes. It definitely is. Here are three types of links you should be building on your website:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>Internal links</strong>: These are links between pages on your website.&nbsp;</li><li><strong>Outbound links</strong>: These are links from your website to another site.</li><li><strong>Inbound links</strong>: These are external links from a website to yours.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>All three types of links are essential to running an impactful SEO campaign. Here are some stats to prove that:</p>\n\n\n\n<p>6. Links are considered among the <a href=\"https://searchengineland.com/now-know-googles-top-three-search-ranking-factors-245882\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">top two criteria</a> used by Google&#8217;s algorithm to rank web pages.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>7. <a href=\"https://ahrefs.com/blog/reciprocal-links/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">43.7% of the top-ranking pages</a> on SERPs have reciprocal links (built when websites link to each other).</p>\n\n\n\n<p>8. <a href=\"https://www.aira.net/state-of-link-building/link-building-measurement-and-reporting/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">52% of digital marketers</a> say link building and brand mentions (also called linkless backlinks) directly impact organic search rankings.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>9. A higher domain rating DR or DA (depending on whether you’re using Semrush, Ahrefs, Moz, or any other SEO tool you&#8217;re using) correlates <a href=\"https://backlinko.com/search-engine-ranking\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">with higher rankings on SERPs</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>10. Sites that rank first on SERPs usually have <a href=\"https://backlinko.com/search-engine-ranking\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">3.8x more backlinks</a> than those on positions 2-10 on the first page.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>11. <a href=\"https://www.aira.net/state-of-link-building/link-building-measurement-and-reporting/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">38% of marketers</a> say page rankings are one of the top key performance indicators (KPIs) they use to gauge the effectiveness of their link-building campaigns.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>12. <a href=\"https://seotribunal.com/blog/stats-to-understand-seo/\">65% of SEOs</a> say link building is the most challenging aspect of SEO.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>13. <a href=\"https://databox.com/how-to-use-internal-links\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">42% of survey respondents</a> said they spend an equal amount of time on building external and <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/features/internal-link-assistant/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">internal links</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"700\" height=\"733\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/link-building-statistics-ahrefs-traffic-study.png\" alt=\"Studies show that there\'s a direct correlation between number of backlinks and traffic.\" class=\"wp-image-88689\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/link-building-statistics-ahrefs-traffic-study.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/link-building-statistics-ahrefs-traffic-study-286x300.png 286w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/link-building-statistics-ahrefs-traffic-study-600x628.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>14. There is a <a href=\"https://ahrefs.com/blog/search-traffic-study/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">direct correlation</a> between the number of backlinks a web page has and the amount of organic traffic it generates.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Popular Link Building Strategies</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Some link building strategies are effective. Others are downright not worth the effort.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Which tactics should you focus on?&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>15. <a href=\"https://userp.io/state-of-backlinks-for-seo/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">40.7% of marketers</a> say content marketing is the best strategy for passively building organic links.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>16. A whopping <a href=\"https://www.aira.net/state-of-link-building/in-house-specific-questions/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">69% of marketers</a> believe buying links can improve a site&#8217;s search rankings</p>\n\n\n\n<p>17. &#8220;Why&#8221; posts, &#8220;What&#8221; posts, and infographics get <a href=\"https://backlinko.com/content-study\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">25.8% more backlinks</a> compared to videos and &#8220;How-to&#8221; posts.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>18. <a href=\"https://aira.net/state-of-link-building/content-led-link-building/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">31% of marketers</a> run outreach campaigns to build links to a new piece of content for up to 4 weeks after launching the content piece. 27% don&#8217;t put an end date to their campaigns.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>19. Guest blogging is one of the most popular and effectual link building practices, with <a href=\"https://www.spiralytics.com/blog/approach-linkbuilding-the-right-way/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">60% of bloggers</a> saying they publish 1-5 guest posts a month.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>The Cost of Link Building in 2022</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>As with all marketing campaigns, you have to invest to see some significant results with link building.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Being an important factor that influences ranking, you must be prepared to invest time and resources in building backlinks.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>How much does link building cost?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>20. <a href=\"https://www.aira.net/state-of-link-building/in-house-specific-questions/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">36% of businesses</a> outsource link building as they see it as a complicated process.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>21. <a href=\"https://www.aira.net/state-of-link-building/in-house-specific-questions/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">61% of marketers</a> say they use up to 10% of their budget on building links.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>22. In a survey of over 800 SEO professionals, about 40% of the respondents said they spend over <a href=\"https://userp.io/state-of-backlinks-for-seo/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">$1000 per month</a> on link building.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>23. In another study, <a href=\"https://www.aira.net/state-of-link-building/in-house-specific-questions/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">46% of marketers</a> said they spend $10,000 or more annually on link building campaigns.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>24. The average cost of buying a backlink is <a href=\"https://ahrefs.com/blog/buy-backlinks/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">$361.44</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>25. <a href=\"https://www.aira.net/state-of-link-building/in-house-specific-questions/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">41% of marketers</a> expect the cost of link building to increase in the coming years.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Disclaimer</strong>: Google is against exchanging links with money or products. That&#8217;s why we don&#8217;t advocate buying links as a link-building tactic. We prefer link building services that build links manually.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Best Content Formats for Link Building</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Content marketing is a discipline with different types of content.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Knowing the content formats that attract the most backlinks is therefore important.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Which content types do just that?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>26. Long-form content gets about <a href=\"https://backlinko.com/content-study\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">77.2% more backlinks</a> than short-form content. This means long-form content should play a central role in your organic link building strategy.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>27. <a href=\"https://contentmarketinginstitute.com/2017/11/types-content-links/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">70% of SEO specialists</a> find data/research to be the most effective content format for attracting links.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>28. Video content ranks among the most linked to content, according to <a href=\"https://seotribunal.com/blog/stats-to-understand-seo/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">66% of survey respondents</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>29. According to the same survey, Infographics (61%) and white papers (60%) are other content format types effective for earning backlinks.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Tips for Building High-quality Backlinks</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>With most marketers struggling with link building, are there some tips to making this important SEO practice easier?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>There sure are. Here are our top four:</p>\n\n\n\n<h3><strong>Become a Resource in Your Niche</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<p>One way to earn backlinks organically is to become a resource in your niche or industry. You can do this by publishing high-quality content. You can also become a trusted resource by using a service like Help a Reporter Out (HARO).</p>\n\n\n\n<h3><strong>Conduct and Publish Industry Research</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Stats. Facts. Data. Research. All these are essential to writing <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/what-is-google-eat/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">authoritative content</a>. Unfortunately, not everyone has the resources and time to conduct original industry research. If you&#8217;re in a position to invest in research, do so. It will help you generate backlinks on autopilot as other publications will cite you in their content.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h3><strong>Fix Broken Links (Or Replace Outdated Ones)</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Every publisher wants to offer their website visitors the best possible experience on their websites. This is why broken links are a nightmare. Also, broken links can hurt your SEO. That&#8217;s why finding and fixing broken links is one of the best tactics you can use to build backlinks. Publishers are more than happy to get help in this regard. The same applies to outdated links.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3><strong>Develop a New Strategy, Technique or Tip</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Another great way of earning organic backlinks is to develop a unique strategy, technique or tip that people in your industry would find helpful. Then, people will link back to your resource on this technique when citing it in their content.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Link Building Statistics: What&#8217;s Next?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>As you&#8217;ve seen from the statistics above, link building is a crucial element of digital marketing. That&#8217;s why every brand must invest in it.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Wondering what to do with all this data?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Simple. This statistic post aims to highlight opportunities and strategies you can leverage to design and execute your next campaign. With links being one of the most critical ranking factors search engines consider, you must ensure your campaigns are effective. For that to happen, you need to design data-driven campaigns.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Successful ink building is a <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/seo-checklist/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">critical element of SEO</a>. The above stats have proven it. But as you&#8217;ve seen, a lot of content online doesn&#8217;t get any backlinks. One reason for that is no one knows about it. To boost the chances of people finding your content and linking back to it, you must create <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/seo-tutorial/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">SEO-friendly content</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>That&#8217;s where SEO plugins like <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">AIOSEO</a> come in.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>AIOSEO is an SEO toolkit that can help you implement <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/seo-best-practices/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">SEO best practices</a> on your website and content. This includes:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>On-page SEO</li><li>Off-page SEO</li><li>Technical SEO</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>With AIOSEO, you can drastically increase the chances of your content ranking without needing to hire an expert.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you&#8217;re not yet an AIOSEO user, there&#8217;s no better time than now to get this powerful plugin. So go ahead and <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">download AIOSEO here</a> and increase your chances of earning backlinks organically.</p>The post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/link-building-statistics/\">29 Link Building Statistics to Help Power Your SEO Strategy</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:49:\"https://aioseo.com/link-building-statistics/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"2\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:2;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:88:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:63:\"How to Write Great SEO Title Tags for Search Engines and People\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:92:\"https://aioseo.com/seo-title-tags/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=seo-title-tags\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:42:\"https://aioseo.com/seo-title-tags/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Tue, 03 May 2022 13:35:07 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:6:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"Blog\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"SEO Tips\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:10:\"meta title\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:10:\"page title\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:14:\"SEO title tags\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:5;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:10:\"title tags\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:27:\"https://aioseo.com/?p=88231\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:425:\"<p>Looking for tips on how to write great title tags? Title tags are an essential component of SEO that most people overlook. However, getting them right can help you drive more clicks on search engine results pages (SERPs). What are&#8230;</p>\nThe post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/seo-title-tags/\">How to Write Great SEO Title Tags for Search Engines and People</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"Kato Nkhoma\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15306:\"<p>Looking for tips on how to write great title tags?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Title tags are an essential component of SEO that most people overlook.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>However, getting them right can help you drive more clicks on search engine results pages (SERPs).</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>What are Title Tags (And Why Do They Matter)?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>A title tag (also called page title, meta title, or SEO title) is an HTML element used to specify the title of a webpage and must not be confused with <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/header-tags/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">header tags</a>. The title tag is located in the head section of a page and looks like this:</p>\n\n\n\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>&lt;title&gt;How to Write Great SEO Title Tags for Search Engines and People&lt;/title&gt;</code></pre>\n\n\n\n<p>A title tag&#8217;s primary purpose is to tell visitors and search engines what to expect from your web page. Here&#8217;s what it looks like on the SERPs:</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"689\" height=\"115\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/seo-title-tags-1.png\" alt=\"SEO title tags are the page titles displayed on search engine results pages.\" class=\"wp-image-88232\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/seo-title-tags-1.png 689w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/seo-title-tags-1-300x50.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/seo-title-tags-1-600x100.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 689px) 100vw, 689px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>As you can see, title tags are part of SERP results snippets, including the URL and meta description.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Why do title tags matter?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here are a few reasons to pay attention to your title tags:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>Increase clickthrough rates (CTR)</strong>: Especially if your title tag shows that your content will meet search intent.</li><li><strong>Helps you rank for your keyword</strong>: Keyword-optimized title tags are an essential on-page SEO element that can <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/seo-best-practices/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">boost your SEO</a>. While title tags may not be a direct ranking factor, they help search bots understand the page&#8217;s content.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<h3>Are Title Tags the Same as H1 Tags?</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Many times, WordPress users confuse title tags and H1 tags.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Are they the same thing?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>While they may look the same, title tags and H1 tags are two different elements. While title tags are HTML elements displayed on SERPs, an H1 tag is the title of the page and is only seen when a visitor clicks through to your page. Therefore, you must create a different title tag to your H1 tag.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Where Does the Title Tag Appear?</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>If the H1 tag appears at the top of a page as the title, where does the title tag appear?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The answer to this question provides insight into why title tags are essential to your SEO campaigns.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>SERPs</strong>: One of the most prominent places title tags appear is on Google&#8217;s search results and other browsers&#8217; SERPs. Their purpose here is to convince searchers to click on your post, as this is the first impression users have of what your content has to offer.&nbsp;</li><li><strong>Browser tab</strong>: Besides the SERPs, your title tag will also appear in the browser tab. Crafted well, users will easily remember it when they need to visit that page again.</li><li><strong>Third-party websites</strong>: External websites and social media platforms usually link to a page using the title tag as the anchor text. This is another reason to get yours right.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Now that you know what a title tag is and why it&#8217;s an important part of your SEO, let&#8217;s get down to the day&#8217;s business — writing effective title tags.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>How to Optimize Your Title Tags Using AIOSEO</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Leaving your title tags to fate is detrimental to your SEO.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Yes, Google does edit and use <a href=\"https://www.searchenginejournal.com/google-changes-more-than-61-percent-of-title-tags/435618/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">its own title tags</a> in some instances, but that doesn&#8217;t mean they&#8217;ll optimize them for you.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>That&#8217;s your responsibility.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Leaving your title tags to fate (and Google) will disadvantage you in the tough competition that&#8217;s on the SERPs. Instead, take time to craft your own optimized title tags. If you use WordPress and the AIOSEO plugin, here&#8217;s how you can do that:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>Step 1</strong>: Scroll to the bottom of the page to the AIOSEO <strong>General Settings </strong>section and find the&nbsp;<strong>Post Title</strong>&nbsp;field.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"700\" height=\"175\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/seo-title-tags-post-title.png\" alt=\"Edit your title tag in the Post Title field under AIOSEO\'s General Settings section.\" class=\"wp-image-88233\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/seo-title-tags-post-title.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/seo-title-tags-post-title-300x75.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/seo-title-tags-post-title-600x150.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>Step 2</strong>: Simply type in your optimized SEO title tag in the field, and that&#8217;s it.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>You can use the tags to define what to include in your title tag, thereby determining how it will look on SERPs. For example, with all three tags in the title, your brand name (or website name) will appear at the end of the title tag. Here&#8217;s what it will look like if you use all three tags:</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"587\" height=\"115\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/seo-title-tags-with-seperator-brand.png\" alt=\"SEO title tag with post title, separator, and site title tags.\" class=\"wp-image-88234\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/seo-title-tags-with-seperator-brand.png 587w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/seo-title-tags-with-seperator-brand-300x59.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 587px) 100vw, 587px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>If you prefer your title tag to appear on SERPs without the separator and site title, you can simply remove the tags in the&nbsp;<strong>Post Title</strong>&nbsp;field.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>8 Tips for Writing Winning SEO Title Tags</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Getting your title tags right is a part of nailing your basic SEO.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>But how do you craft a good title tag that results in more organic traffic to your content?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Let&#8217;s quickly jump into our eight tips for writing excellent SEO title tags for search engines and people.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>1. Watch the Character Limit</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>One of the first things to note and be careful about concerning title tags is to follow the prescribed character range. Best practices dictate 60-70 characters to avoid your title tag being cut off on SERPs.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"627\" height=\"125\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/seo-title-tags-truncated.png\" alt=\"SEO title tags with too many characters can get truncated on SERPs.\" class=\"wp-image-88236\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/seo-title-tags-truncated.png 627w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/seo-title-tags-truncated-300x60.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/seo-title-tags-truncated-600x120.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 627px) 100vw, 627px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>In the example above, the title is too long and thus got truncated. As a result, the user is unsure what the page is about. This leads to poor clickthrough rates. These signal to search engines that it&#8217;s a low-quality page. On the other hand, a higher CTR results in your page ranking higher.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>2. Be Specific and Descriptive</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Remember, your title tells what your page is about. Because of this, your title tag must be as specific and descriptive as possible. Doing so ensures that there&#8217;s no confusion about the page&#8217;s purpose.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Your page title should also be unique to avoid cannibalization. This is when two pages have the same or similar target keywords, resulting in shared traffic. Creating unique titles helps ensure search engines don&#8217;t confuse pages with similar keywords (like product pages). Doing so ensures that each page is displayed for the most relevant search query.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>3. Craft Compelling Title Tag Copy</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The primary purpose of title tags is to get users to click on your page or post on SERPs. Because of this, it must be compelling. Consider it an elevator pitch — your one shot at getting users to take action. A few tips for creating persuasive title tag copy include using:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>Verbs</strong>: Action words help elicit a response from users.&nbsp;</li><li><strong>Power words</strong>: These are words that elicit an emotional response from the reader. If a reader has an emotional connection with your title, the chances of clicking on your post are increased.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>While it may be a tiny element of your copy, the title tag plays a huge role in the success of your digital marketing. That&#8217;s why you must take the time to craft effective title tags.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>4. Use Your Primary Keyword Strategically</h3>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/best-seo-keyword-analysis-tool\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Keywords</a> are one of the foundational aspects of SEO. They also play an essential role in crafting effective title tags. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>The best way to strategically use your important keywords in your title tags is to frontload them. You should put it as close to the beginning of the title tag as possible. One thing you should avoid is keyword stuffing. Also, don&#8217;t use variations of your keyword in the title tag. This is a black SEO tactic that leads to poor user experience.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>5. Prove Search Intent and Topical Relevance</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Search intent is another element of impactful SEO. It simply means the reason behind a user&#8217;s search, and Google&#8217;s new algorithms consider it when ranking content.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Knowing why users search for a particular keyword is essential in helping you create content they find helpful.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>How can users know that your content will answer their questions?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>By crafting your title tag so that it proves search intent.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To do this, your title tag must be topically relevant. In addition, it must give users the confidence to click into your article, knowing they&#8217;ll be satisfied with the content.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>6. Write for Users First</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>One of the biggest mistakes people make with SEO is to think it&#8217;s all about search bots. Because of this, all optimization is done to rank well on SERPs, neglecting users in the process.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Optimizing for search bots and neglecting users is not proper SEO.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/seo-hacks-to-grow-your-traffic/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Effective SEO</a> takes users into account as well. After all, what&#8217;s the point of ranking high yet generating no traffic?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>That&#8217;s why, when crafting your title tags, do so for users first. When you write for users first, you increase the chances of users engaging with your content. One of the most important engagement metrics influenced by title tags is clickthrough rates.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To write title tags that are users centric:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Avoid keyword stuffing</li><li>Be descriptive</li><li>Ensure your title makes logical sense</li><li>Readability and memorability are key</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Never put search engines before users. While this may give you some wins, they&#8217;re usually temporary as search engines prefer content that provides users with a positive experience.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>7. Highlight What Makes Your Content Unique</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Another tip for writing excellent SEO title tags is highlighting what makes your content unique. With over <a href=\"https://www.worldometers.info/blogs/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">8 million blog posts</a> competing for attention every day, being unique will help you stand out. It&#8217;s a necessity if you want to up your SEO and content marketing game.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"542\" height=\"383\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/seo-title-tags-number-of-blog-posts.png\" alt=\"With over 8 million blog posts published every day, you must ensure your title tags are unique.\" class=\"wp-image-88240\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/seo-title-tags-number-of-blog-posts.png 542w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/seo-title-tags-number-of-blog-posts-300x212.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 542px) 100vw, 542px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>To increase your chances of your resource being picked on SERPs, highlight what sets you apart from others.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>8. Use Curiosity to Encourage Clicks</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>People are naturally curious. As a marketer or blogger, you can use this to your advantage by crafting curiosity-driven title tags.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>One way to do this is to apply a curiosity gap. Curiosity gaps refer to the space between what users know and what they want to know.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Creating a curiosity gap involves giving readers a hint of what they&#8217;ll find in the article. While it&#8217;s not easy to do with the limited character count recommended for title tags, with a bit of creativity, you can pull it off.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Don&#8217;t Neglect Your SEO Title Tags!</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Never leave title tags as an afterthought. Plan for them and craft effective ones for each page and post you create. Sure, they may not impact your SEO as much as other heavy-hitting strategies like link building. However, the little impact it makes can make a huge difference in your SEO strategy.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You should also consider revisiting the posts you&#8217;ve already published and crafting optimized title tags for them. This is probably one of the most underrated&nbsp;<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://aioseo.com/seo-checklist/\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">SEO tips</a>&nbsp;that can give you an edge over your competitors.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To make this easier, you&#8217;ll need an SEO plugin like AIOSEO. AIOSEO is a powerful toolkit that can help you implement most SEO best practices without hiring an expert.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you haven&#8217;t downloaded AIOSEO yet, there&#8217;s no better time than now. So go ahead and&nbsp;<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">get it here</a>.&nbsp;</p>The post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/seo-title-tags/\">How to Write Great SEO Title Tags for Search Engines and People</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:39:\"https://aioseo.com/seo-title-tags/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:3;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:85:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:68:\"Divi SEO: How to Optimize Your Divi Site with the AIOSEO Integration\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:80:\"https://aioseo.com/divi-seo/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=divi-seo\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:36:\"https://aioseo.com/divi-seo/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang