bsite platform, but you need a website hosting service to<a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/guides/\"> build a WordPress website</a> unless you&#8217;re very tech-savvy. You don’t need to use one specifically for WordPress, but it’ll improve your site performance if you do.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3><strong>What Types of Web Hosting Services Are There?</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<p>There are <a href=\"https://www.techradar.com/web-hosting/what-are-the-different-types-of-web-hosting\">six basic types of web hosting services</a>: Shared Hosting, Virtual Private Server (VPS), Dedicated Server, Cloud Hosting, Managed Hosting, and Colocation. The type you should get depends on what functionalities your business needs.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong><em>Note: </em></strong><em>Some web hosting companies use “shared hosting” and “managed hosting” somewhat interchangeably, so they may say “shared” when they actually mean “managed.” Be sure to read the fine print.</em></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Below, you can learn a bit about the different types of WordPress hosting options available, including which (if any) of our favorites offer these plans. We’ve left out colocation because it’s just a rented space rather than a host in and of itself.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-container-627ace1d5cb7d wp-block-group is-style-decorated\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table alignfull is-style-stripes\"><table><tbody><tr><td><strong>Type</strong></td><td><strong>Description</strong></td><td><strong>Best For</strong></td><td><strong>Offered By</strong></td></tr><tr><td><strong>Shared WordPress Hosting</strong></td><td>Site shares servers with other sites using the same resources (RAM, CPU, etc.); often come with valuable tools</td><td>Startups with entry-level needs on a budget</td><td><a class=\"thirstylink\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"A2 Hosting\" href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/a2-hosting/\" data-shortcode=\"true\">A2 Hosting</a><br><a class=\"thirst